{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The participants in our experiment were students who were familiar with computer science.",
    "Their overall accuracy in identifying the authorship of texts was approximately 76%.",
    "While this is significantly above chance level, it is not as accurate as one might hope, given the normally accepted level of false positives in psychological experiments of 5%.",
    "Guo et al. (2023) showed that when humans have to distinguish between texts of AI origin and human origin, if the texts are presented one by one, performance is lower than when the texts are presented in pairs.",
    "This strategy could be adopted by experimenters to increase performance in identification."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Guo et al. (2023) showed that when humans have to distinguish between texts of AI origin and human origin, if the texts are presented one by one, performance is lower than when the texts are presented in pairs."
  ]
